    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer870706664" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17764416829039834906">Rating: 4.5* of five<br/><br/>I hate, loathe, detest reviewing Kindle books. It&apos;s clunky. How should I know which bookmarked passage is mine? I have to look all over the damned place and usually end up annoyed so I can&apos;t quote the good bits.<br/><br/>That&apos;s why I&apos;ve never reviewed my Goodreads friend Blake Crouch&apos;s eerie thriller <i>Pines</i>. It&apos;s set in Idaho, which is scary enough for me right there with all the right-wingers and Mormons (hi Pat, sending smooches, please don&apos;t shoot me), in an imaginary town called Way</span>
  <span id="freeText17764416829039834906" style="display:none">Rating: 4.5* of five<br /><br />I hate, loathe, detest reviewing Kindle books. It's clunky. How should I know which bookmarked passage is mine? I have to look all over the damned place and usually end up annoyed so I can't quote the good bits.<br /><br />That's why I've never reviewed my Goodreads friend Blake Crouch's eerie thriller <i>Pines</i>. It's set in Idaho, which is scary enough for me right there with all the right-wingers and Mormons (hi Pat, sending smooches, please don't shoot me), in an imaginary town called Wayward Pines *cough*Coueur d'Alene*cough*. It's a <a href="http://tinyurl.com/kqk4rwr" rel="nofollow noopener">$2 Kindle purchase</a> today.<br /><br />It's worth twice that and more. It will keep you clicking the next button until way past your bedtime.</span>
