        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer743548499" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15277637372660056421"><blockquote>
  <b>YESTERDAY IS HISTORY.<br/>TOMORROW IS A MYSTERY.<br/>TODAY IS A GIFT.<br/>THATâ€™S WHY ITâ€™S CALLED THE PRESENT.<br/>WORK HARD, BE HAPPY, AND ENJOY YOUR<br/>LIFE IN WAYWARD PINES!</b>
</blockquote><br/><br/>There is an absolute plethora of excellent reviews out there for this series so I really did not think I would write one. Â But how can I not? Â Â This story blew me away and that is quite a significant statement when you consider that I had already watched the TV series.<br/><br/>Secret Service Agent, Ethan Burke was sent to Wayward Pines, Idaho to locate</span>
  <span id="freeText15277637372660056421" style="display:none"><blockquote>
  <b>YESTERDAY IS HISTORY.<br />TOMORROW IS A MYSTERY.<br />TODAY IS A GIFT.<br />THATâ€™S WHY ITâ€™S CALLED THE PRESENT.<br />WORK HARD, BE HAPPY, AND ENJOY YOUR<br />LIFE IN WAYWARD PINES!</b>
</blockquote><br /><br />There is an absolute plethora of excellent reviews out there for this series so I really did not think I would write one. Â But how can I not? Â Â This story blew me away and that is quite a significant statement when you consider that I had already watched the TV series.<br /><br />Secret Service Agent, Ethan Burke was sent to Wayward Pines, Idaho to locate and recover two federal agents who have been missing for a month. Â Â Shortly after his arrival he is involved in a car accident, one that leaves his partner dead and lands him in the hospital.<br /><br />Without ID, wallet or cell phone Ethan is at the mercy of the residents of this small community. Â It is a beautiful place, with idyllic little residential streets and beautiful Victorian homes surrounded by magnificent forests and breathtaking cliffs; nature resplendent everywhere. Â But not everything is as it seems. Â There is something not quite right here. Â For one it would seem that no-one knows where his personal belongings have got to, people are reluctant to help or even believe who he is and when he finally does track down one of the missing agents, he can scarce believe his eyes. Â She seems to have aged a decade or more in just a few weeks and despite the fact that they once shared an intimate relationship, she too, is reluctant to talk or answer Ethanâ€™s questions. <br /><br />Every attempt he makes to contact his wife or his office is unsuccessful. Â No one calls him back.<br /><br />What in hell is going on here?<br /><br />Desperate now to get out of Wayward Pines, Ethan steals a vehicle but no matter which route he takes it would seem that all roads lead back to Wayward Pines. And now he is really on the Sheriff's shit list.<br /><br />I really do not want to say too much, since if you have not yet read this or seen the excellent TV series it is best that you wade into these waters with as little knowledge as possible. Â <br /><br />I will say that it kept me furiously turning pages, scratching my head and on the edge of my seat. Â The big reveals as you start turning into the home lap are masterfully handled, effectively closing out this chapter of the story and leaving you nail biting, anxious to start the next book in the trilogy. Â <br /><br />Blake Crouch says that he was inspired to write this by David Lynchâ€™s iconic television series Twin Peaks which aired when he was twelve years old. Â We can only hope that Mr. Crouchâ€™s work will also someday inspire a future writer. Â <br /><br />Yes, yes I am, already part way through book two!</span>
  <a data-text-id="15277637372660056421" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


